                    <h1>Enrollment</h1>
                    <ul>
                        <li>This program must be offered at your child's School/Preschool to enroll.</li>
                        <li>Children must be at least 3 years old when enrolling for the program.</li>
                        <li>No new students may enroll after 8th week of a session.</li>
                        <li>After this time students have missed too much information
                        to participate in the program or to participate in a final show.</li>
                        <li>If a parent wishes to remove their child from the Kids’ Play Program, that parent must submit a cancellation 
                        notice to <a href="mailTo:Amanda@kidsplaytheatre.com">Amanda@kidsplaytheatre.com</a> cancellation notice must include child's
                        name, date of birth, school name, parent name, phone number and cancellation date. </li>
                        <li>Parents who cancel enrollment are entitled to reimbursement for 
                        paid future classes; however, previous payments for classes that have been fulfilled will not be reimbursed.</li>
                        <li>For the protection of the Kids’ Play staff and the students involved in the Kids’ Play Program; if at any time a 
                        student is deemed violent or disruptive by the Kids Play teacher, The Kids Play teacher has the right to have the 
                        child removed from the class.</li>
                        <li>If necessary, Kids Play reserves the right to remove students from the program for any reason. If the child is 
                        involuntarily removed from the program, the parents are entitled to reimbursement for paid future classes, however, 
                        previous payments for classes that have been fulfilled will not be reimbursed.</li>
                        <li>By enrolling in the Kids Play program you give your permission for photographs and/or video footage of your child 
                        to be used for promotional purposes on the web, print and in visual media.</li>
                        <li>All employees from Kids Play have gone through background checks and Kids Play employees have experience working with children and a background in theatre.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <h1>Make-up classes</h1>
                    Makeup classes cannot be scheduled for individual students who are absent from class.<br />
                    If the Kids Play teacher is absent or if the school is closed due to a holiday or for inclement 
                    weather, a make-up day will be rescheduled.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <h1>Payment</h1>
                    To enroll, you may register and make a payment online <a href="Payments.aspx">here.</a><br />
                    Or, you can complete the enrollment form and return it to your child’s school with payment. 
                    All checks should be made out to Kids Play.
                    <br />
                    <br />
